{
  "texts": [
    "Gemma 3 27B showed the largest observed adjustment, reducing its summarization-condition GSES score from 21 to 10 after three follow-up prompts (Appendix Table 2).",
    "Claude Sonnet 4 exhibited relatively low expressed certainty in several conditions, triggering multiple follow-up queries, but did not change its numeric GSES scores in those sessions.",
    "Overall, follow-up prompts led to modest, predominantly conservative revisions and suggest that first-pass self-assessments are somewhat over-confident for a subset of modeltask combinations.",
    "All LLMs scored correctly in the Computational and Social Tasks (100%).",
    "Responses to the Summarization Task had mixed results across the models (mostly due to key elements missing in comparison to gold standard summaries, see rubric under Appendix Table 3)."
  ]
}